abstract: The former vice president had a lot to prove. To those who had written him off after the first debate, he had this to say: “malarkey.”
snippet: The former vice president had a lot to prove. To those who had written him off after the first debate, he had this to say: “malarkey.”
lead_paragraph: One month after a wobbly debate performance that reinforced the perceived weaknesses of the ostensible front-runner — Is he too old? Too nostalgically moderate? Too politically brittle to defend himself when challenged? — former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. settled behind his center-stage lectern on Wednesday night and supplied some answers: He is still old. He is still nostalgic. And he is still the front-runner, until someone can prove otherwise.

abstract: Mr. Biden, the front-runner, was confronted over his record on health care and criminal justice, and this time not just from Kamala Harris.
snippet: Mr. Biden, the front-runner, was confronted over his record on health care and criminal justice, and this time not just from Kamala Harris.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. delivered a steadfast defense of his moderate policies in the Democratic primary debate on Wednesday, striking back at a familiar adversary, Senator Kamala Harris, but facing intensifying attacks on his record from liberal rivals including Senator Cory Booker and Julián Castro, the former housing secretary.

abstract: Our reporters are following all of the exchanges. They will be fact-checking the candidates and providing context and explanation for the policy debates.
snippet: Our reporters are following all of the exchanges. They will be fact-checking the candidates and providing context and explanation for the policy debates.
lead_paragraph: The second round of Democratic debates was completed on Wednesday night in Detroit, with 10 candidates onstage for the second of two back-to-back nights. The other 10 candidates who qualified for the debates appeared Tuesday on the same stage.

headline_main: Analysis of Night 2 of the July Democratic Debates

abstract: The candidates along the wings went hard after the night’s leading candidates, Joe Biden and Kamala Harris.
snippet: The candidates along the wings went hard after the night’s leading candidates, Joe Biden and Kamala Harris.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — Wednesday’s debate was barely underway when the attacks began on former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and Senator Kamala Harris, and some of their Democratic rivals rarely let up.

headline_main: The Debates in Detroit: A Big Field, a Sprawling Circus and Lots of Porta Potties
byline_original: By Lisa Lerer and Reid J. Epstein

abstract: Mr. Prince helped bring to life a stunning lineup of shows: “Cabaret,” “Sweeney Todd,” and Broadway’s longest-running spectacle, “The Phantom of the Opera.”
snippet: Mr. Prince helped bring to life a stunning lineup of shows: “Cabaret,” “Sweeney Todd,” and Broadway’s longest-running spectacle, “The Phantom of the Opera.”
lead_paragraph: Hal Prince, the Broadway royal and prodigious Tony winner who produced or directed (and sometimes both) many of the most enduring musicals in theater history, including “West Side Story,” “Fiddler on the Roof,” “Cabaret,” “Sweeney Todd” and “The Phantom of the Opera,” the longest-running show in Broadway history, died on Wednesday in Reykjavik, Iceland. He was 91.
